The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Saturday, October 01, 2005 

 On a turning track, offer as much of the bat as possible

 Work on your fitness... Physical strength leads to mental strength

Cricket Online 

 Ravi Shastri 

 I am a right-handed batsman. I often misjudge the balls that are to be left outside the off-stump. What rule should I follow when judging such balls?

 (Dhairya Desai, 11, Calcutta-25) 

 Check your guard. Also your footwork should be assured. Watch the ball closely and play late.

 I always have a fear element lurking at the back of my mind when facing a pacer. How can I get rid of this?

 (Lalitesh Vikram, 18, Calcutta-39) 

 Think positively. Always keep your eyes on the ball and be prepared to take a few knocks.It will toughen you up.

 I am a right-handed batsman. I always fail to deliver under pressure. What is the secret to be successful under such circumstances?

 (Santosh Mondal, 19, Birbhum) 

 Your mindset is the key here. Believe in your ability and think positively. A weak mind is the problem here.

 I am a right-handed batsman. I often get bowled by yorkers. Please help.

 (Tathagat Banerjee, 16, Bankura) 

 Watch the ball and your backlift.

 I am right-arm mediumpacer. What is the difference between a off-cutter and an out-swinger?

 (Debarshi Mukherjee, Calcutta-61) 

 Off-cutter comes in to you after pitching if you are a right-hander and the out-swinger goes away from you in the air. This is if a right-hander is bowling and you are a right-handed batsman.

 On a turning track, is it wise to use more of the pad than the bat against spinners?

 (Tapan Roy, 19, Calcutta-41) 

 Offer as much of the bat as possible. 

 I am a right-handed batsman. I am often adjudged leg-before against leg breaks. Please help.

 (Rohit Bhattacharya, 22, Calcutta-16) 

 Get the footwork right and use your bat as much as possible.

 I am a right-handed batsman. How can I maintain my concentration at the start of every session?

 (Sanjib Datta, 23, Calcutta) 

 Keep talking to yourself. Take the net sessions seriously and work on your fitness. Physical strength leads to mental strength.

 I am a right-arm medium pacer. Though I bowl an off-stump line, my deliveries constantly fall short of length despite my best efforts to pitch the ball up. Please help.

 (Srinivas, 18, Jamshedpur) 

 Watch the spot where you want the ball to land and stay as high as possible in your action. 

 I am a mediumpacer. Are gym sessions (especially weight training) necessary during a tournament?

 (Prabal Dey, 19, Calcutta) 

 Light work during the season. Hard workouts during off-season.




